caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3816125" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/YNOT-2025-line-up.-CREDIT_-Press.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="2500" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/YNOT-2025-line-up.-CREDIT_-Press.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/YNOT-2025-line-up.-CREDIT_-Press-400x500.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/YNOT-2025-line-up.-CREDIT_-Press-800x1000.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/YNOT-2025-line-up.-CREDIT_-Press-696x870.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/YNOT-2025-line-up.-CREDIT_-Press-1392x1740.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/YNOT-2025-line-up.-CREDIT_-Press-1068x1335.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3816125" class="wp-caption-text"> YNOT 2025 阵容。图片来源：新闻界</figcaption></figure><p>音乐节董事总经理贾森·奥克利 (Jason Oakley) 表示：“去年的 Y Not 音乐节在很多方面都令人难以置信，我要感谢所有来参加的人、我们出色的支持者和所有表演者！ 2025 年看起来会更好——我们非常兴奋地告诉大家，The Prodigy、Courteeners 和 Madness 将成为头条新闻，而 The Wombats 也将在周四晚上占据主导地位。我们为大家准备了又一个重要的一年，阵容包括《原始尖叫》、《最后的晚宴》、《安妮·麦克》、《西格丽德》、《马克西莫·帕克》等等……再见？！”</p><p>去年的版本中，<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/jamie-t">杰米·T (Jamie T)</a> 、<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/noel-gallaghers-high-flying-birds">诺埃尔·加拉格尔 (Noel Gallagher) 的 High Flying Birds</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/kaiser-chiefs">Kaiser Chiefs</a>等乐队登上了舞台。</p><p> 《 <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/y-not-2025-the-prodigy-courteeners-madness-the-wombats-top-line-up-3816122">Y Not 2025：The Prodigy、Courteeners、Madness、The Wombats》顶级阵容</a>首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
波格斯夫妇畅谈围绕“纽约童话”的文化战争https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-pogues-speak-out-on-the-culture-wars-that-surround-fairytale-of-new-york-3816110?u tm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=the-pogues 畅谈围绕纽约童话故事的文化战争Laura MolloyTue, 26 Nov 2024 17:08:37 +0000 Music NewsNewsChristmasFolk https://www.nme.com/?p=3816110 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/The-Pogues-perform-at-Glastonbury-in-1986.-CREDIT_-Michael-Putland_Getty-Images.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/The-Pogues-perform-at-Glastonbury-in-1986.-CREDIT_-Michael-Putland_Getty-Images.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/The-Pogues-perform-at-Glastonbury-in-1986.-CREDIT_-Michael-Putland_Getty-Images-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/The-Pogues-perform-at-Glastonbury-in-1986.-CREDIT_-Michael-Putland_Getty-Images-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/The-Pogues-perform-at-Glastonbury-in-1986.-CREDIT_-Michael-Putland_Getty-Images-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/The-Pogues-perform-at-Glastonbury-in-1986.-CREDIT_-Michael-Putland_Getty-Images-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/The-Pogues-perform-at-Glastonbury-in-1986.-CREDIT_-Michael-Putland_Getty-Images-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> “时代在变，你必须更加注意自己所说的内容以及说话的时间”</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-pogues-speak-out-on-the-culture-wars-that-surround-fairytale-of-new-york-3816110">波格斯 (The Pogues) 谈论围绕《纽约童话》的文化战争的</a>帖子首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">《NME》</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/The-Pogues-perform-at-Glastonbury-in-1986.-CREDIT_-Michael-Putland_Getty-Images.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/The-Pogues-perform-at-Glastonbury-in-1986.-CREDIT_-Michael-Putland_Getty-Images.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/The-Pogues-perform-at-Glastonbury-in-1986.-CREDIT_-Michael-Putland_Getty-Images-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/The-Pogues-perform-at-Glastonbury-in-1986.-CREDIT_-Michael-Putland_Getty-Images-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/The-Pogues-perform-at-Glastonbury-in-1986.-CREDIT_-Michael-Putland_Getty-Images-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/The-Pogues-perform-at-Glastonbury-in-1986.-CREDIT_-Michael-Putland_Getty-Images-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/The-Pogues-perform-at-Glastonbury-in-1986.-CREDIT_-Michael-Putland_Getty-Images-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-pogues">波格斯乐队</a>在<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-pogues-interview-tour-shane-macgowan-fontaines-d-c-kneecap-irish-music-fairytale-new-york-lyrics-controversy-3814660"><em>NME</em>的新采访</a>中谈到了围绕他们的歌曲《纽约童话》的文化战争。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-pogues-interview-tour-shane-macgowan-fontaines-d-c-kneecap-irish-music-fairytale-new-york-lyrics-controversy-3814660">波格斯夫妇：“Fontaines DC 举着自己的火炬，Kneecap 是史无前例的”</a></strong></li></ul><p>这首 1987 年圣诞歌曲由<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/kirsty-maccoll">Kirsty MacColl</a>和 The Pogues 主唱<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/shane-macgowan">Shane McGowan</a>演唱，由于歌词中使用了仇视同性恋的脏话<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/some-people-are-calling-for-the-word-f-t-to-be-removed-from-fairytale-of-new-york-2417374">，近年来一直处于争论的中心</a>。</p><p> 2018 年<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/some-people-are-calling-for-the-word-f-t-to-be-removed-from-fairytale-of-new-york-2417374">，麦高恩为这个词进行了辩护，称这个词从来没有恐同的意思</a>，尽管两年后， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/bbc-defends-decision-to-play-censored-fairytale-of-new-york-on-radio-1-2828233">BBC 广播电台 1 宣布他们将在圣诞节前夕播放经过审查的版本</a>， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/bbc-radio-2-to-play-fairytale-of-new-york-without-offensive-lyric-for-first-time-3359118">而 BBC 广播电台 2 也在 2022 年采取了这一举措</a>。</p><p>这一决定引起了一些人的批评，其中包括<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/nick-cave">尼克·凯夫（Nick Cave）</a> ，他表示<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/nick-cave-on-fairytale-of-new-york-row-2828589">删除这个词“在最重要和最鲁莽的时刻削弱了歌曲的价值，从而毁了这首歌，剥夺了它的价值。”</a></p><p> 2019 年， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/gavin-stacey-ruth-jones-homophobic-slur-christmas-special-2591576">演员兼编剧露丝·琼斯 (Ruth Jones) 在《加<em>文与史黛西》(Gavin &amp; Stacey)</em>将这首歌词纳入当年的圣诞电视特别节目后也面临强烈反对</a>。当 Nessa（琼斯饰演）和 Bryn 表演 1987 年热门歌曲的版本时，就发生了这种诽谤。 </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="The Pogues - 纽约童话（官方视频）" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/j9jbdgZidu8?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p>在 BBC 最初宣布他们将审查这首歌词后，劳伦斯·福克斯 (Laurence Fox) 在 Twitter 上批评了广播公司， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-pogues-slam-laurence-fox-as-herrenvolk-shite-after-fairytale-of-new-york-backlash-2820672">促使乐队的官方账户回击他</a>，写道：“滚开你这个小赫伦沃尔克狗屎。” Herrenvolk 是纳粹意识形态中的一个概念，将德国人民称为“优等种族”。</p><p>现在， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-pogues-interview-tour-shane-macgowan-fontaines-d-c-kneecap-irish-music-fairytale-new-york-lyrics-controversy-3814660">在接受<em>NME 采访时，</em></a>波格斯乐队的幸存成员詹姆斯·费恩利 (James Fearnley)、杰姆·费纳 (Jem Finer) 和斯皮德·史黛西 (Spider Stacy) 参与了这场年度辩论。</p><p>当被问及乐队对围绕这首歌的文化战争有何看法时，史黛西提到了与福克斯的公开争吵，她说：“我们不想代表像劳伦斯·福克斯这样的人被卷入任何事情。”</p><p>他接着说：“当 BBC 宣布他们要审查这首歌词时，我正在看 Twitter，上面有一个人说他喜欢 The Pogues，但每年圣诞节，当他听到喝醉的家伙在街上喊出这个词时，他们跟着唱《纽约童话》——他想起了自己在学校因为同性恋而被开除的次数。</p><p> “我个人的观点是，人们不应该忍受这一点，所以我亲自表示我们同意 BBC 的决定。时代在变，你需要更加注意自己所说的内容以及说话的时间。” </p><figure id="attachment_3578695" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3578695" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3578695" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/shane-macgowan-the-pogues-spider-stacy.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/shane-macgowan-the-pogues-spider-stacy.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/shane-macgowan-the-pogues-spider-stacy-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/shane-macgowan-the-pogues-spider-stacy-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/shane-macgowan-the-pogues-spider-stacy-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/shane-macgowan-the-pogues-spider-stacy-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/shane-macgowan-the-pogues-spider-stacy-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3578695" class="wp-caption-text"> 2013 年 12 月 15 日，英国曼彻斯特，The Pogues 乐队的 Shane MacGowan、Darryl Hunt 和 Spider Stacy 在 Apollo 舞台上表演（图片来源：Shirlaine Forrest/WireImage）</figcaption></figure><p>芬纳接着补充道：“如果这些台词是在戏剧中传达的，那就不一样了，但是一首歌把歌词放进人们嘴里，让人们醉醺醺地唱着，他们甚至可能没有意识到自己在唱什么，但突然间它就出现在了地铁站里。</p><p> “因此，尽管肖恩没有写一首恐同的小曲，而且他在任何方面都不是恐同的——他写的是一个会这样说话的角色——如果它在一个可能被断章取义和伤害的环境中播放人们以任何方式，那么这个词被替换或发出嘟嘟声就很公平了。我们对此没有任何问题。”</p><p>当被问到他们是否会现场演唱原歌词时，史黛西表示乐队将“让歌手自己选择”，然后补充道：“因为已经有替代品了，我不知道为什么肖恩一开始就没有这样做——这就是<em>虚张声势</em>。如果他一开始就这样做，我们就会在美国大受欢迎。”</p><p>他们还谈到了去年 11 月<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/shane-macgowan">Shane MacGowan</a>去世后， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/fans-are-rallying-to-get-the-pogues-fairytale-of-new-york-to-christmas-number-one-after-death-of-shane-macgowan-3551355">由粉丝主导的歌曲首次登上第一名的活动</a>。芬纳告诉我们，乐队对于获得这一荣誉“并不在意”，并补充道：“这更多的是唱片公司的事情。这没有任何意义。”</p><p>史黛西接着说：“它不需要它。 《纽约童话》没有成为第一，有点像[著名足球运动员]约翰·克鲁伊夫和乔治·贝斯特都没有赢得世界杯！”</p><p>凯尔特人偶像最近<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-pogues-announce-2025-uk-and-ireland-tour-celebrating-40-years-of-rum-sodomy-the-lash-3813788">宣布了他们 13 年来的首次重大巡演</a>，也是自肖恩·麦高恩<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/shane-macgowan">(Shane MacGowan)</a>去世以来的首次巡演，其中将包括原成员费恩利 (Fearnley)、芬纳 (Finer) 和史黛西 (Stacy)，以及替补已故主唱的嘉宾阵容。</p><p>您可以<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-pogues-interview-tour-shane-macgowan-fontaines-d-c-kneecap-irish-music-fairytale-new-york-lyrics-controversy-3814660">在此处</a>阅读完整的对话。</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-pogues-speak-out-on-the-culture-wars-that-surround-fairytale-of-new-york-3816110">波格斯 (The Pogues) 谈论围绕《纽约童话》的文化战争的</a>帖子首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">《NME》</a>上。</p> ;
